Comment: Another game form this project vs the tournament mastermind himself.  I feel that this game has a rather important theme to it, because not have I fallen for it but I believe that many of my fellow chess players have as well.  When attacking it is important to consider the safety of ones own king.  Don't rush forward at all cost.  Also, goes with the theme to play patiently even when far down in material.
This is the start of this lovely tourney black wins the queen! With Nxg4.  White then regains the knight by forking king and knight.

Ne6 seems to be rather popular among the other players so far in this tourney due to the the chance to possibly at a later date exchange the knight for bishop.  I wanted to attempt to free up my dsb, but black ends up locking it in.
e5 questions the stability of my knight and bishop.  Being that f4 will fall soon.  Either by exchange fxe5 Bxe5 (though I don't see what good that does.) or by exf4.
